            {
                "id": "The First Chest_2102152366208",
                "name": "The First Chest",
                "event_type": "Event",
                "pos": [
                    524.912014056414,
                    -511.73177586619516
                ],
                "markdown": "## The First Chest\n\nThe chest sits wedged beneath a collapsed section of railing, its iron clasp rusted into a permanent scowl. Frank has to kick it twice before the lid groans open, exhaling a breath of stale, river-damp air.\n\nInside, nestled in a bed of mildewed cloth:\n\n- **A tarnished pocket watch** \u2014 its face cracked, the hands frozen at **3:17**. There are initials engraved on the back, but the corrosion makes them almost impossible to read. Almost. Frank tilts it toward the light. *R. D.* \u2014 or maybe *R. B.*? He pockets it.\n- **A coil of rope**, knotted in a way that looks deliberate \u2014 not sailor's knots, something else. Something practiced.\n- **A half-empty bottle of whiskey**, the label long since peeled away. The liquid inside has turned the color of weak tea.\n- **A folded piece of paper**, pressed flat against the bottom of the chest. The ink has bled and faded, but Frank can make out fragments \u2014 a list of some kind. Names? Locations? The water damage has stolen most of it, but one word survives intact near the bottom, circled twice:\n\n  ***\"Upstream.\"***\n\nFrank stares at the word for a long moment. The river is dry now. There is no upstream anymore.\n\nBut there *was*.",
                "stage_notes": "",
                "selected_characters": [],
